    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i see. so if the empirical evidence generally points toward increased wealth concentration, isn't it kind of misleading to present the \"trickle-down\" perspective as a valid alternative in a serious academic context? like, shouldn't we treat that view more as a debunked theory rather than a side with equal weight?",
